Robert Edward Bercich (born November 9, 1936 in Chicago, Illinois) is a former American football safety in the National Football League for the Dallas Cowboys. He played college football at Michigan State University and was drafted in the fifteenth round of the 1959 NFL Draft by the New York Giants. 
